Russian Equity Movers: Razgulay, TNK-BP, Transneft, Uralkali

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-07-26T16:10:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/russian-equity-movers-razgulay-tnk-bp-transneft-uralkali.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slid 0.3
percent to 1,722.11 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index added 0.4 percent to 1,987.79.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Razgulay (GRAZ RX), the Russian sugar producer, climbed
to its highest level in more than two weeks, adding 2.6 percent
to 49.64 rubles. White sugar gained by as much as $18, or 2.3
percent, to $815.40 a metric ton on the NYSE Liffe in  London .  TNK-BP (TNBP RX) jumped to its highest in more than a week,
rising 0.9 percent to 90.04 rubles after BP Plc’s Russian oil
venture said profit almost doubled in the second quarter on
higher prices for crude.  OAO Transneft (TRNFP RX) advanced for the sixth day after
 Russia ’s oil-pipeline operator said first-quarter net income
more than doubled to 84.9 billion rubles ($3.1 billion)
according to international accounting standards. Its shares
gained 2.1 percent to 44,221 rubles, the highest close in more
than three months.  OAO Uralkali (URKA RX) declined to for a second day after
OAO Acron’s chairman, Alexander Popov, said it may sell a third
of its 2.7 percent stake in Russia’s largest potash maker. Its
shares slid 0.4 percent to 274.27 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
